rComments: Birdiest course of all time. The lectures are basically just a space to talk casually and have fun. As long as you speak French moderately well and know even a little bit about the course this is accompanying, you cannot mess up at all.

Attending his lectures is kind of useless and he gives no feedback on anything. With that said, the course is literally a guaranteed A+ if you put in a little effort. You can tell he enjoys teaching and loves his students, but online teaching really is not his forte.

He's great. If you can choose him, take him. He's great. No cons, no negative anything. Easy tests, literally show up and pass with an A minimum. He's very caring also and helpful and all you want. Stop reading and just take him, you won't regret it

Super kind and caring professor, makes everyone feel comfortable. Definitely one of my favourite courses and one that I learnt a lot from. Would recommend this professor and course to everyone looking to learn french.
